    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="123"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.61333/275a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Columbia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>700. At meeting of the Inter-American Coffee Board on May 25, the Colombian
                    delegate stated that although Colombia would like to continue participating in
                    the Inter-American Coffee Agreement, it could not approve continuation of the
                    Agreement unless the Board were to recommend to the signatory governments that
                    Colombia’s participation in the quotas be increased. He suggested that
                    Colombia’s share in the quotas be raised to 24 percent. The United States
                    delegate declined to take a position as to whether or not Colombia’s share in
                    the quotas should be increased. There was no support for the Colombian proposal
                    on the part of delegates from other of the producing countries.</p>
                <p>The Board adjourned to meet again on May 31. In the absence of further action by
                    the Board this is the last day on which participating <pb facs="0163" n="149"
                        xml:id="pg_149"/> governments may notify the Board of their decision with
                    respect to continuation under the resolution adopted by the Board in its meeting
                    of April 4, extending the notification period in accordance with Article XXIV of
                    the Agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
